parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Brake and Traction Control Module Communication Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic brake and traction control module communication can cause the loss of traction control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: code shows the reason for the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door master power switch can cause the loss of window and lock functionality, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of their speed, leading to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer does not register correct speed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: relay 46 (headlamp driver module) burns up and damages additional fuses and relays.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Lock and Gear Shift Indicator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock and gear shift indicator can cause inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Door locks start unlocking and locking rapidly
gear shift indicator on the dash goes from drive to park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge sensor can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel depletion, engine stalling, and potentially leaving the driver stranded, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: showing empty or low fuel levels even when the tank is full
the gauge fluctuates up and down
the low fuel warning light is constantly on
the vehicle stalls or hesitates while accelerating
and the fuel level indicator needle moves erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of headlights while driving can cause a loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights turn off or dim without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight relay can cause the headlights to turn off or malfunction, leading to a loss of visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights turn off or dim without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights dim with heated seats or heater on
voltage gauge drops and then returns to normal
